59. dentque, ‘further': so osten in Lucr. This new point is not easy to follow: it is not obvious that fear of death is the cause of avarice and ambition. It has been noticed, eg. by Thucydides, that morality is relaxed in times of epidemic disease; but Lucr. is not thinking of exceptional circumstances.
